image.altText: A group of Matildas footballers jump together in delight, celebrating a big win at the Women's World Cup.

items.synopsis: The Matildas beat France 7-6 in a dramatic sudden-death penalty shootout in Brisbane, with Mackenzie Arnold and Courtnee Vine the heroes. Follow all the updates in our live blog.

title.children: England and Colombia all square, Matildas beat France in sudden death penalty shootout

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Alessia Russo! A lovely through ball from Georgia Stanway - a bit of fortune in the way the ball has fallen to her - but a sublime finish across the face of goal into the far corner. The defender could have done better. She should have done better really. But in the end it matters not because England have taken the lead. There has been some nice passing moves in the last 10 minutes or so from England as they grow in confidence. Has the goal been coming? A bit.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 63' ENGLAND TAKES THE LEAD!

children.content: Alessia Russo! A lovely through ball from Georgia Stanway - a bit of fortune in the way the ball has fallen to her - but a sublime finish across the face of goal into the far corner.
The defender could have done better.
She should have done better really.
But in the end it matters not because England have taken the lead.
There has been some nice passing moves in the last 10 minutes or so from England as they grow in confidence.
Has the goal been coming? A bit.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: A pretty even half all things considered. England have had seven shots on goal, four of them on target, Colombia five - with just the one on the money. The Lionesses have had the majority of the possession as well, 67 to 32. But we are all square at the break - and no wiser as to who will be meeting the Matildas in Sydney next week.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Half time: England 1-1 Colombia

children.content: A pretty even half all things considered.
England have had seven shots on goal, four of them on target, Colombia five - with just the one on the money.
The Lionesses have had the majority of the possession as well, 67 to 32.
But we are all square at the break - and no wiser as to who will be meeting the Matildas in Sydney next week.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Oh no, that's a horrible way to give away an equaliser. Lucy Bronze finds Alessia Russo in the penalty area, who stabbed a weak effort straight to Catalina Pérez, but the Colombian keeper inexplicably fumbles it straight back to Russo, the ball squirts out to Lauren Hemp, who stabs home. Appalling keeping really and England are level!
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 45+5' GOAL ENGLAND!

children.content: Oh no, that's a horrible way to give away an equaliser.
